Fair_compensation_tax_text: The original works by artists were created with their own art supplies (eg tablets). Purchasing those art supplies requires funding, although some artists earn money by selling their art (therefore they are able to invest in art supplies)some do not sell theirs but still want share their art with the people). AI then uses those art. I think it is almost like ‘’discrediting” and “robbing” the artists. The point is, money is still needed to create art, no matter how much. AI being fed with art freely doesn’t help support the artists. The artists work that are used should be recognized and supported with payment so they may gain some profit. Hence, taxing. Does this make any sense?
